      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden, ¶ Christmas eve ¶ 1870 ¶  ¶ Let me thank you, dear Sir Redmond, for your friendly letter of this day, and for your wishes to support me in my researches, through the public Libr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <ab rend="number"
                style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: -1in; hyphenate: false; break-before: page; "
                type="heading">70.12.24c</ab>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Redmond Barry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">VPRS 5486/P0/1, inward correspondence, official letters miscellaneous p. 126, VA 913 Public Library of Victoria, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Christmas eve</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1870</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-indent: 0.3333in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me thank you, dear Sir Redmond, for your friendly letter of this day, and for your wishes to support me in my researches, through the public Library.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>On one point you are under a wrong impression, namely that the Government gradually provides books for my Department. When I was so ill in 1867 I wrote you from Queenscliff<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic. Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that such is not the case, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not a single book</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been purchased on public expense for my Department for 5 years past; so all had to come out of my slender income. When 5 years ago the Government purchased my library, I only asked half the second hand value of the books. I think that I am right in asserting, that for a series of years past scarcely a single book was purchased for the public library of those, suggested &amp; required by me. I am sure you will deem it fair, that an equitable share of the fund available should be given also to the phytologic section, at the same time when the other divisions of the Library are provided.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to R. Barry, 24 December 1870<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 70-12-24b), for M's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>suggestions of botanical works that the Library should acquire.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With my best wishes for a joyful new year</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I am just pleasingly surprised in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>obtaining copies of the able adress, delivered by you in Ballarat<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
